legations.</span></li><li value="3" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Disciplinary Hearing:</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> The employee has the right to be accompanied by a colleague or trade union representative.</span></li><li value="4" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Outcome:</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> A written decision will be provided, which may include:</span></li><li value="5" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><ul class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListUnordered"><li value="1" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">First Written Warning</span></li><li value="2" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Final Written Warning</span></li><li value="3" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Dismissal (for gross misconduct)</span></li></ul></li><li value="5" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Appeal:</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> The employee has the right to appeal the decision.</span></li></ol><h2 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3. Grievance Procedure</span></h2><h3 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading3" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Informal Resolution</span></h3><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Employees are encouraged to raise concerns informally with their line manager first.</span></p><h3 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading3" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Formal Grievance</span></h3><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">If informal resolution is not possible:</span></p><ol class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListOrdered"><li value="1" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Submit in Writing:</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> The employee should submit their grievance in writing.</span></li><li value="2" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Grievance Meeting:</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> A meeting will be held to discuss the grievance. The employee has the right to be accompanied.</span></li><li value="3" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Outcome:</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> A written response will be provided.</span></li><li value="4" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Appeal:</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> The employee has the right to appeal the decision.</span></li></ol><h2 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">4. Record Keeping</span></h2><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">All disciplinary and grievance records will be kept confidential and stored securely for the duration required by law.</span></p>	published	47	\N	\N	{}		Employment & HR	2025-11-30 15:36:17.100987	2025-11-30 15:36:17.100987	2025-11-3