_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><br></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This document outlines a process for how The Ambassador Platform will ensure the following:</span></p><ul class="_editorListUnordered_1q1gx_133"><li value="1" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Security incident events</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> are detected, reported, and monitored consistently.</span></li><li value="2" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Incidents</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> are assessed and responded to appropriately.</span></li><li value="3" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Action</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> is taken to reduce the impact of a breach.</span></li><li value="4" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Relevant breaches</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> are reported to the Information Commissioner within the 72-hour window.</span></li><li value="5" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Improvements</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> are made to prevent recurrence.</span></li><li value="6" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Improvements</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> are communicated to the wider organization.</span></li></ul><h3 class="_editorHeading3_1q1gx_95" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Responsibilities</span></h3><h4 class="_editorHeading4_1q1gx_104" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">2.1. Directors</span></h4><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The Directors of the organization have responsibility for ensuring that any security risks are managed appropriately and that risks are identified and appropriately managed.</span></p><h4 class="_editorHeading4_1q1gx_104" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">2.2. All Staff</span></h4><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">All users of information assets across the organization should familiarize themselves with this procedure, be aware of security risks, and be vigilant in order to ensure breaches are identified, reported, and managed in a timely manner.</span></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><i><em class="_editorTextItalic_1q1gx_168" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Gross negligence and intentional violations</em></i><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> (including not reporting incidents/mistakes) are taken seriously and will lead to disciplinary action.</span></p><h3 class="_editorHeading3_1q1gx_95" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Procedures</span></h3><h4 class="_editorHeading4_1q1gx_104" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.1. Identify a Incident Response/Suspected Incident Response</span></h4><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A security incident can happen for a number of reasons, for example:</span></p><ul class="_editorListUnordered_1q1gx_133"><li value="1" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Hacking attack</strong></b></li><li value="2" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Equipment failure</strong></b></li><li value="3" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Human error</strong></b></li></ul><h4 class="_editorHeading4_1q1gx_104" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.2. Reporting an Incident</span></h4><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">It is vital that as soon as an Incident is identified or suspected it is immediately reported to the Data Protection Team.</span></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">As much information as is immediately available should be collated and the </span><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Incident Response Notification Form</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> (</span><i><em class="_editorTextItalic_1q1gx_168" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Appendix A</em></i><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">) should be completed and sent via Basecamp as soon as possible (latest within 12 hours of breach identification) to the Director of Engineering (DSO) and CEO (DDOS).</span></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The Director of Engineering and CEO will analyze the form, update the Incident Response Log, and ascertain whether any immediate corrective/containment/escalation actions are required.</span></p><h4 class="_editorHeading4_1q1gx_104" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.3. Investigating an Incident</span></h4><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The incident will be assessed. The investigation will:</span></p><ul class="_editorListUnordered_1q1gx_133"><li value="1" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Establish the nature of the incident, the type, and impact.</span></li><li value="2" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Perform a risk assessment.</span></li><li value="3" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Identify actions the organization needs to take to eliminate the incident.</span></li><li value="4" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Assess the ongoing risk and actions required to prevent a recurrence of the incident.</span></li></ul><h4 class="_editorHeading4_1q1gx_104" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.4. Escalation</span></h4><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The Incident Response Log will be reviewed on a regular basis by the board of the company who will determine whether any updates to policy and procedures are required and coordinate any relevant training.</span></p><h4 class="_editorHeading4_1q1gx_104" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.5. Reporting an Incident to a Customer</span></h4><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The Director of Engineering will coordinate breach reporting to the Information Commissioner and to all customers as soon as possible, at least within 72 hours via email and phone (if needed).</span></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">An incident is also reflected automatically at </span><a href="https://status.theambassadorplatform.com/" class="_editorLink_1q1gx_153" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">status.theambassadorplatform.com</span></a><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> and a customer can sign-up to receive automatic notifications via email, Slack, RSS.</span></p><h2 class="_editorHeading2_1q1gx_86" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Appendix A  Incident Response Notification Form</span></h2><ul class="_editorListUnordered_1q1gx_133"><li value="1" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Date</strong></b></li><li value="2" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><b><strong 