81	40	Yuriy Omelchuk 	edit	42	2025-11-14 01:58:19.314034	{"changes": {"tags": [], "title": "Yuriy Omelchuk ", "status": "published", "content": "<p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">CONSULTING AGREEMENT No. 4-0620jjjjj</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><br><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">THIS CONSULTING AGREEMENT (the \\"Agreement\\") is made and entered into this</span><br><i><b><strong class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextItalic\\" style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">Month date, year (the \\"Effective Date\\")</strong></b></i><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\"> by and between PCS EU B.V., whose Registered Address is Amsterdam, Herengracht 420, 1017BZ (hereinafter referred to as the Company\\") and</span><br><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">Individual entrepreneur Name Surname who resides at: Postcode, Country, Street address, (hereinafter referred to as the \\"Consultant\\").</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">WHEREAS, the Company wishes to engage the Consultant to provide the services described herein and Consultant agrees to provide the services for the compensation and otherwise in accordance with the terms and conditions contained in this Agreement.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the foregoing, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged, accepted and agreed to, the Company and the Consultant, intending to be legally bound, agree to the terms set forth below.</span></p><h2 class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">1 TERM</span></h2><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">Commencing as of the Effective Date, and continuing permanently (the Term), unless earlier terminated pursuant to Article 5 hereof.</span></p><h2 class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">2 Duties and Services</span></h2><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(a) Consultant's duties and responsibilities shall be (collectively, the Duties or Services):</span></p><ul class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListUnordered\\"><li value=\\"1\\" class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">Consulting on software development/delivery process including people involved, duties and roles, processes and practices, and tools.</span></li><li value=\\"2\\" class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">Assistance in hiring, performance review, team composition.</span></li></ul><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(b) The Company will periodically provide the Consultant with a schedule of the requested responsibilities and deliverables for the applicable period of time. The Duties will be scheduled on an as-needed basis.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(c) The Consultant represents and warrants to the Company that he is under no contractual or other restrictions or obligations which are inconsistent with the execution of this Agreement, or which will interfere with the performance of his Duties. Consultant represents and warrants that the execution and performance of this Agreement will not violate any policies or procedures of any other person or entity for which he performs Services concurrently with those performed herein.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(d) In performing the Services, Consultant shall comply, to the best of his knowledge, with all business conduct, regulatory and health and safety guidelines established by the Company for any governmental authority with respect to the Companys business.</span></p><h2 class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">3 Consulting Fee</span></h2><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(a) Description of the Services to be performed under this Agreement stipulated by the parties by e-mail.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(b) The fees shall be negotiated by the Parties in any convenient for them forms. The Parties acknowledge that the amount of Consultants fees for provided services for each month is determined by the amount of money, received on bank account of Consultant and based on a respective invoice. The funds may be transferred partly during the mentioned period. If the Consultant does not agree with the amount of received money it may issue a claim to the Company within 10 days.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(c) The Consultant agrees that all Services will be rendered by him as an independent contractor and that this Agreement does not create an employer-employee relationship between the Consultant and the Company. The Consultant shall have no right to receive any employee benefits including, but not limited to, health and accident insurance, life insurance, sick leave and/or vacation. Consultant agrees to pay all taxes including, self-employment taxes due in respect of the Consulting Fee.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(d) If the Consultant wishes to suspend the provision of services without terminating this Agreement, he shall notify the Company at least 14 days before the desired date of suspension of services.</span></p><h2 class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">4 Company Materials</span></h2><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(a) The Company shall provide the Consultant, on his request, with all instructions , information, materials, guidance etc. reasonably required for the proper performance of the Services. Company can buy software upon Consultants request if such software is needed to provide services under this agreement.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(b) The Consultant acknowledges and accepts that all information, materials, inventions, software code, algorithms, ideas, designs , processes, discovery, original works of authorship, development , improvements , trade secret, concept, or other proprietary information provided by the Company to the Consultant under this Agreement for the purposes of the performance of the Services ( the Companys Materials ) shall remain the exclusive property of the Company.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(c) Upon termination of this Agreement, or whenever requested by the Company , the Consultant shall immediately deliver to the Company , and shall not keep in the Consultants possession , recreate, or deliver to anyone else , any and all Companys property , including all Companys materials without any limits , other Inventions and all devices and equipment belonging to the Company , all electronically-stored information and passwords to access such property.</span></p><h2 class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">5 Termination of the Agreement</span></h2><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(a) If the Consultant voluntarily ceases performing his Duties, becomes physically or mentally unable to perform his Duties, or is terminated for cause, then, in each instance, the Consulting Fee shall cease and terminate as of such date.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(b) First three months from the Effective Date shall be deemed as a probationary period during which the Company may terminate this Agreement at any time without prior notice of the Consultant.</span><br><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">After expiration of probationary period, the Company may terminate this Agreement upon not less than 14 calendar days prior notice.</span><br><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">In case Consultant conducts significant breach of the Agreement or renders services of poor quality which results or could result in negative consequences for the Company, the Company may terminate the Agreement at any time without prior notice of Consultant.</span><br><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">The Consultant may terminate this Agreement at any time upon not less than 30 calendar days prior written notice of the Company.</span><br><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(c) Upon termination under Sections 5(a) or 5(b), neither party shall have any further obligations under this Agreement, except for the obligations which by their terms survive this termination as noted in Section 7 hereof. Upon termination and, in any case, upon the Companys request, the Consultant shall return immediately to the Company all Confidential Information, as hereinafter defined, and copies thereof.</span></p><h2 class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">6 Restricted Activities</span></h2><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">During the Term and for a period of one (1) year thereafter, Consultant will not, directly or indirectly:</span><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(i) solicit or request any employee of or consultant to the Company or any of its affiliated companies to leave the employ of or cease consulting for the Company;</span><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(ii) solicit or request any employee of or consultant to the Company or any of its affiliated companies to join the employ of, or begin consulting for, any individual or entity that researches, develops, markets or sells products that compete with those of the Company or any of its affiliated companies;</span><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(iii) solicit or request any individual or entity that researches, develops, markets or sells products that compete with those of the Company or any of its affiliated companies, or any of the Clients of the Company to employ or retain as a consultant any employee or consultant of the Company or any of its affiliated companies; or</span><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(iv) induce or attempt to induce any supplier or vendor of the Company or any of its affiliated companies to terminate or breach any written or oral agreement or understanding with the or any of its affiliated companies.</span></p><h2 class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">7 Confidential Information</span></h2><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(a) Definitions.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">For the purposes of this Article, the terms set forth below shall have the following meanings:</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(b) Confidential Information. For the purposes of this Agreement, Confidential Information shall mean and collectively include: all information relating to the business, plans and/or technology of the Company including, but not limited to technical information including inventions, methods, plans, processes, specifications, characteristics, assays, raw data, scientific preclinical or clinical data, records, databases, formulations, clinical protocols, equipment design, know-how, experience, and trade secrets; developmental, marketing, sales, Company, supplier, consulting relationship information, operating, performance, and cost information; computer programming techniques whether in tangible or intangible form, and all record bearing media containing or disclosing the foregoing information and techniques including, written business plans, patents and patent applications, grant applications, notes, and memoranda, whether in writing or presented, stored or maintained in or by electronic, magnetic, or other means.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(c) The Consultant further agrees that he shall not disclose his retention as an independent Consultant or the terms of this Agreement to any person without the prior written consent of the Company and shall at all times preserve the confidential nature of its relationship to the Company and of the Services.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(d) During the term of this Agreement and after Expiration or termination hereof, the Consultant shall hold in the strictest confidence , and take all reasonable precautions to prevent any unauthorized use or disclosure of the Confidential information , and the Consultant shall Not (i) use the Confidential information for any purposes whatsoever other then as necessary for the performance of the Services for the benefit of the Company , and/or (ii) disclosure the Confidential information to any third party without the written consent of the Company. The Consultant may disclose the Confidential information to the extent compelled by applicable law, provided however , prior to such disclosure , the Consultant shall provide prior written notice to the Company and seek a protective order or such similar confidential protection as may be available under applicable law. The Consultant agrees that no ownership of the Confidential Information is conveyed to the Consultant.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(e) NonDisclosure to Third Parties. Except as required by Consultant's Duties, Consultant shall not, at any time now or in the future, directly or indirectly, use, publish, disseminate or otherwise disclose any Confidential Information, Concepts, or Ideas to any third party without the prior written consent of the Company which consent may be denied in each instance and all of the same, together with publication rights, shall belong exclusively to the Company.</span></p><h2 class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">8 Intellectual Property Rights</span></h2><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(a) Definitions. For the purposes of this Article, the terms set forth below shall have the following meanings:</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(b) Concept and Ideas. All concepts and ideas disclosed by the Company to Consultant or which are first developed by Consultant during the course of the performance of Services hereunder or those which relate to the Company' present, past or prospective business activities, services, and products, shall remain the sole and exclusive property of the Company. The Consultant shall have no publication rights and all of the same shall belong exclusively to the Company.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(c) Documents, etc. All documents, diskettes, tapes, procedural manuals, guides, specifications, plans, drawings, designs and similar materials, lists of present, past or prospective Companys, Company proposals, invitations to submit proposals, price lists and data relating to the pricing of the Company' products and services, records, notebooks and all other materials containing Confidential Information or information about Concepts or Ideas (including all copies and reproductions thereof), that come into Consultant's possession or control by reason of Consultant's performance of the relationship, whether prepared by Consultant or others: (a) are the property of the Company, (b) will not be used by Consultant in any way other than in connection with the performance of his Duties, (c) will not be provided or shown to any third party by Consultant, (d) will not be removed from the Company's or Consultants premises (except as Consultant's Duties require), and (e) at the termination (for whatever reason), of Consultant's relationship with the Company, will be left with, or forthwith returned by Consultant to the Company.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">Patents, etc. The Consultant agrees that the Company is and shall remain the exclusive owner of the Confidential Information and Concepts and Ideas. Any interest in patents, patent applications, inventions, technological innovations, trade names, trademarks, service marks, copyrights, copyrightable works, developments, discoveries, designs, processes, formulas, know-how, data and analysis, whether registrable or not (\\"Developments\\"), which Consultant, as a result of rendering Services to the Company under this Agreement, may conceive or develop, shall: (i) forthwith be brought to the attention of the Company by Consultant and (ii) belong exclusively to the Company. No license or conveyance of any such rights to the Consultant is granted or implied under this Agreement.</span><br><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">Assignment. The Consultant hereby assigns and, to the extent any such assignment cannot be made at present, hereby agrees to assign to the Company, without further compensation, all of his right, title and interest in and to all Concepts, Ideas, and Developments under this Agreement. The Consultant will execute all documents and perform all lawful acts which the Company considers necessary or advisable to secure its rights hereunder and to carry out the intent of this Agreement.</span><br><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">The parties have agreed that all exclusive intellectual property rights which will be created in the course of the performance by the Consultant of this Agreement, including those as provided Bern Convention on Protection of Works of Literature and Art ( Paris Act of 24.07.1971, as amended and restated on 02.10.1979), Universal Copyright Convention (1952), as well as other international legislative legal acts , in particular :</span><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">- right to use the object of intellectual property,</span><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">- exclusive right to allow the use of intellectual property,</span><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">- exclusive right to prevent illegal use of the intellectual property object , including prohibition thereof,</span><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">- and other rights both currently existing and which may exist in the future ,</span><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">shall be owned by the Company.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(g) The Companys exclusive property right to the objects of the intellectual property as created in course performance by the Consultant by this Agreement shall apply to both finished objects of intellectual property, and materials received when developing the same , relative derivative audio-visual reflections , notwithstanding the language and form of expression , including the initial text and objective code.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(h) The Consultant shall assist the Company and/or its designees in every proper way to secure the Companys rights in Inventions and related intellectual property rights in all countries. The Consultant shall execute all documents and other instruments that the Company deems necessary to apply for and obtain these rights and to assign to the Company the sole and exclusive rights , title , and interest in and to the Inventions , and any related intellectual property rights . The Consultants obligation to provide assistance shall continue after the termination or expiration of this Agreement. The Consultant shall not register or apply for registration , in his name or any third partys name , any intellectual property rights (in any country ) related to the inventions.</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">(i) The Consultant hereby transfers and assigns fully and irrevocably to the Company the exclusive proprietary rights therein ( including those owned jointly with third parties , if any, including without limitation (i) the right to use the inventions, (ii)the right to authorize the use of the inventions, (iii) the right to prevent ( prohibit) any improper or unauthorized use of the Inventions , and (iv) any other proprietary rights contemplated by applicable law.</span></p><h2 class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">9 Headings</span></h2><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">Headings and subheadings are for convenience only and shall not be deemed to be a part of this Agreement.</span></p><h2 class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">10 Amendments</span></h2><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">This Agreement may be amended or modified, in whole or in part, only by an instrument in writing signed by all parties hereto. Any amendment, consent, decision, waiver or other action to be made, taken or given by the Company with respect to the Agreement shall be made, taken or given on behalf of the Company.</span></p><h2 class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">11 Notices</span></h2><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">All notices, requests, claims, demands and other communications under this Agreement shall be in writing or email and shall be deemed given if delivered personally or sent by overnight courier or email to the parties at the addresses (email) set forth below (or at such other address for a party as shall be specified by like notice, or email that parties usually use during providing of services).</span></p><h2 class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">16 Counterparts</span></h2><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">This Agreement may be executed in two or more counterparts, each of which shall constitute an original and all of which shall be deemed a single agreement.</span></p><table class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTable\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><colgroup><col><col></colgroup><tbody><tr dir=\\"ltr\\"><th class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader\\" dir=\\"ltr\\" style=\\"border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);\\"><h3 class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading3\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">COMPANY</span></h3></th><th class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader\\" dir=\\"ltr\\" style=\\"border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);\\"><h3 class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading3\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">CONSULTANT</span></h3></th></tr><tr dir=\\"ltr\\"><th class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader\\" dir=\\"ltr\\" style=\\"border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);\\"><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">Company Name: PCS EU B.V.</span><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">Title: Director</span><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">Name: Alexander van der Laan</span></p><p class=\\"c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph\\" dir=\\"ltr\\"><br><span style=\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\">Signature:__________________________