3" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Expectations regarding communication and response times.</span></li><li value="4" class="_editorListItem_1a9kc_143" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Performance evaluation metrics.</span></li></ul><h2 class="_editorHeading2_1a9kc_82" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">6. Technology and Equipment</span></h2><p class="_editorParagraph_1a9kc_64" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The organization will provide necessary technology support and equipment, subject to availability and budget considerations. Employees are responsible for maintaining this equipment in good condition and ensuring that sensitive information is safeguarded.</span></p><h2 class="_editorHeading2_1a9kc_82" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">7. Data Security and Confidentiality</span></h2><p class="_editorParagraph_1a9kc_64" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Employees are expected to adhere to the organization's data security protocols. This includes using secure connections and networks, maintaining confidentiality of information, and avoiding the use of personal devices for accessing company data unless explicitly authorized.</span></p><h2 class="_editorHeading2_1a9kc_82" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">8. Performance and Supervision</span></h2><p class="_editorParagraph_1a9kc_64" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Regular performance reviews will be conducted to ensure remote work does not adversely affect productivity and output. Supervisors shall schedule regular check-ins to discuss performance, address any challenges, and provide support as needed.</span></p><h2 class="_editorHeading2_1a9kc_82" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">9. Work Environment</span></h2><p class="_editorParagraph_1a9kc_64" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Employees are required to maintain a professional and distraction-free work environment that is conduci