are required to maintain a professional and distraction-free work environment that is conducive to performing their job responsibilities effectively. This includes having a suitable workspace, chair, and lighting.</span></p><h2 class="c1c__module__editorHeading2" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">10. Compliance and Review</span></h2><p class="c1c__module__editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Human Resources shall ensure compliance with this policy and related legal obligations. The policy will undergo periodic reviews to ascertain its effectiveness and relevance in light of changing circumstances and regulatory landscapes.</span></p><h2 class="c1c__module__editorHeading2" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">11. Exceptions</span></h2><p class="c1c__module__editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Any exceptions to this policy must be reviewed and approved by the Human Resources department on a case-by-case basis, with appropriate documentation and justification.</span></p><h2 class="c1c__module__editorHeading2" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">12. Disciplinary Actions</span></h2><p class="c1c__module__editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Non-compliance with the provisions of this policy may result in disciplinary action, up to and including termination of employment, in accordance with the organization's disciplinary procedures.</span></p><p class="c1c__module__editorParagraph"><br></p>	draft	2025-08-19	2025-08-19	{hr}	Human resources	Compliance	t	f	\N	8	2025-08-20 07:29:55.167956	3	\N
