extBold_1knvi_162" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Action Taken</strong></b></p></th></tr><tr dir="ltr"><th class="_editorTableCell_1knvi_198 _editorTableCellHeader_1knvi_206" style="border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);"><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">17.02.2025</span></p></th><th class="_editorTableCell_1knvi_198 _editorTableCellHeader_1knvi_206" style="border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);"><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">23:11</span></p></th><th class="_editorTableCell_1knvi_198 _editorTableCellHeader_1knvi_206" dir="ltr" style="border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);"><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">some passwords related to old and unused domains have been compromised</span></p></th><th class="_editorTableCell_1knvi_198 _editorTableCellHeader_1knvi_206" dir="ltr" style="border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);"><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">These emails were created on a Google Workspace account that is used as an identity provider. Therefore, when the passwords for these emails were compromised, Google, which continuously monitors password safety, automatically informed us about it.</span></p></th><th class="_editorTableCell_1knvi_198 _editorTableCellHeader_1knvi_206" dir="ltr" style="border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);"><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">George Olesen, CEO</span></p></th><th class="_editorTableCell_1knvi_198 _editorTableCellHeader_1knvi_206" dir="ltr" style="border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);"><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">7 records</span></p></th><th class="_editorTableCell_1knvi_198 _editorTableCellHeader_1knvi_206" dir="ltr" style="border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);"><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">none. mostly system emails were used for demo accounts - nothing related to customer data, PII, or sensitive information</span></p></th><th class="_editorTableCell_1knvi_198 _editorTableCellHeader_1knvi_206" dir="ltr" style="border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);"><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">dashboard.theambassadorpaltform.com</span></p></th><th class="_editorTableCell_1knvi_198 _editorTableCellHeader_1knvi_206" dir="ltr" style="border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);"><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">password to emails</span></p></th><th class="_editorTableCell_1knvi_198 _editorTableCellHeader_1knvi_206" dir="ltr" style="border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);"><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">MITM Attack or Weak or Reused Passwords and Lack of Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) as these accounts were not related to any real customer or any other form of sensitive information.</span></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Definitely not</span></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">a credential exposure from a 3-party breach (tested on respective services that validate it)</span></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A phishing attack</span></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Malware or key logger</span></p></th><th class="_editorTableCell_1knvi_198 _editorTableCellHeader_1knvi_206" dir="ltr" style="border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);"><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Employees warned</span></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Passwords updated</span></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">MFA installed</span></p></th></tr></tbody></table><p class="_editorParagraph_1knvi_66"><br></p>	draft	\N	\N	{}			f	f	\N	14	2025-10-01 10:21:58.60785	5	\N
53	15	1	Disciplinary and Grievance Policy	<h1>Disciplinary and Grievance Policy</h1>\n<h2>1. Purpose</h2>\n<p>This policy outlines the procedures for handling disciplinary matters and employee grievances to ensure fairness and consistency, in line with the Acas Code of Practice.</p>\n<h2>2. Disciplinary Procedure</h2>\n<h3>Informal Action</h3>\n<p>Minor misconduct will be addressed informally through discussion and counselling.</p>\n<h3>Formal Action</h3>\n<p>For more serious issues, the following stages will be followed:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Investigation:</strong> A fair and impartial investigation will be conducted.</li>\n<li><strong>Written Notification:</strong> The employee will be notified in writing of the allegations.</li>\n<li><strong>Disciplinary Hearing:</strong> The employee has the right to be accompanied by a colleague or trade union representative.</li>\n<li><strong>Outcome:</strong> A written decision will be provided, which may include:<ul>\n<li>First Written Warning</li>\n<li>Final Written Warning</li>\n<li>Dismissal (for gross misconduct)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Appeal:</strong> The employee has the right to appeal the decision.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>3. Grievance Procedure</h2>\n<h3>Informal Resolution</h3>\n<p>Employees are encouraged to raise concerns informally with their line manager first.</p>\n<h3>Formal Grievance</h3>\n<p>If informal resolution is not possible:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Submit in Writing:</strong> The employee should submit their grievance in writing.</li>\n<li><strong>Grievance Meeting:</strong> A meeting will be held to discuss the grievance. The employee has the right to be accompanied.</li>\n<li><strong>Outcome:</strong> A written response will be provided.</li>\n<li><strong>Appeal:</strong> The employee has the right to appeal the decision.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>4. Record Keeping</h2>\n<p>All disciplinary and grievance records will be kept confidential and stored securely for the duration required by law.</p>\n	draft	\N	