nowledge, with all business conduct, regulatory and health and safety guidelines established by the Company for any governmental authority with respect to the Companys business.</span></p><h2 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3 Consulting Fee</span></h2><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">(a) Description of the Services to be performed under this Agreement stipulated by the parties by e-mail.</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><br><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">(b) The fees shall be negotiated by the Parties in any convenient for them forms. The Parties acknowledge that the amount of Consultants fees for provided services for each month is determined by the amount of money, received on bank account of Consultant and based on a respective invoice. The funds may be transferred partly during the mentioned period. If the Consultant does not agree with the amount of received money it may issue a claim to the Company within 10 days.</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><br><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">(c) The Consultant agrees that all Services will be rendered by him as an independent contractor and that this Agreement does not create an employer-employee relationship between the Consultant and the Company. The Consultant shall have no right to receive any employee benefits including, but not limited to, health and accident insurance, life insurance, sick leave and/or vacation. Consultant agrees to pay all taxes including, self-employment taxes due in respect of the Consulting Fee.</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">(d) If the Consultant wishes to suspend the provision of services without terminating this Agreement, he shall notify the Company at least 14 days before the desired date of suspension of services.</span></p><h2 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">4 Company Materials</span></h2><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">(a) The Company shall provide the Consultant, on his request, with all instructions , information, materials, guidance etc. reasonably required for the proper performance of the Services. Company can buy software upon Consultants request if such software is needed to provide services under this agreement.</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">(b) The Consultant acknowledges and accepts that all information, materials, inventions, software code, algorithms, ideas, designs , processes, discovery, original works of authorship, development , improvements , trade secret, concept, or other proprietary information provided by the Company to the Consultant under this Agreement for the purposes of the performance of the Services ( the Companys Materials ) shall remain the exclusive property of the Company.</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">(c) Upon termination of this Agreement, or whenever requested by the Company , the Consultant shall immediately deliver to the Company , and shall not keep in the Consultants possession , recreate, or deliver to anyone else , any and all Companys property , including all Companys materials without any limits , other Inventions and all devices and equipment belonging to the Company , all electronically-stored information and passwords to access such property.</span></p><h2 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">5 Termination of the Agreement</span></h2><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">(a) If the Consultant voluntarily ceases performing his Duties, becomes physically or mentally unable to perform his Duties, or is terminated for cause, then, in each instance, the Consulting Fee shall cease and terminate as of such date.</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><br><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">(b) First three months from the Effective Date shall be deemed as a probationary period during which the Company may terminate this Agreement at any time without prior notice of the Consultant.</span><br><br><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">After expiration of probationary period, the Company may terminate this Agreement upon not less than 14 calendar days prior notice.</span><br><br><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">In case Consultant conducts significant breach of the Agreement or renders services of poor quality which results or could result in negative consequences for the Company, the Company may terminate the Agreement at any time without prior notice of Consultant.</span><br><br><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The Consultant may terminate this Agreement at any time upon not less than 30 calendar days prior written notice of the Company.</span><br><br><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">(c) Upon termination under Sections 5(a) or 5(b), neither party shall have any further obligations under this Agreement, except for the obligations which by their terms survive this termination as noted in Section 7 hereof. Upon termination and, in any case, upon the Companys request, the Consultant shall return immediately to the Company all Confidential Information, as hereinafter defined, and copies thereof.</span></p><h2 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">6 Restricted Activities</span></h2><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">During the Term and for a period of one (1) year thereafter, Consultant will not, directly or indirectly:</span><br><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">(i) solicit or request any employee of or consultant to the Company or any of its affiliated companies to leave the employ of or cease consulting for the Company;</span><br><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">(ii) solicit or request any employee of or consultant to the Company or any of its affiliated companies to join the employ of, or begin consulting for, any individual or entity that researches, develops, markets or sells products that compete with those of the Company or any of its affiliated companies;</span><br><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">(iii) solicit or request any individual or entity that researches, develops, markets or sells products that compete with those of the Company or any of its affiliated companies, or any of the Clients of the Company to employ or retain as a consultant any employee or consultant of the Company or any of its affiliated companies; or</span><br><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">(iv) induce or attempt to induce any supplier or vendor of the Company or any of its affiliated companies to terminate or breach any written or oral agreement or understanding with the or any of its affiliated companies.</span></p><h2 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">7 Confidential Information</span></h2><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">(a) Definitions.</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">For the purposes of this Article, the terms set forth below shall have the following meanings:</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><br><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">(b) Confidential Information. For the purposes of this Agreement, Confidential Information shall mean and collectively include: all information relating to the business, plans and/