hite-space: pre-wrap;"> The employee has the right to be accompanied by a colleague or trade union representative.</span></li><li value="4" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Outcome:</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> A written decision will be provided, which may include:</span></li><li value="5" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><ul class="_editorListUnordered_1q1gx_133"><li value="1" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">First Written Warning</span></li><li value="2" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Final Written Warning</span></li><li value="3" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Dismissal (for gross misconduct)</span></li></ul></li><li value="5" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Appeal:</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> The employee has the right to appeal the decision.</span></li></ol><h2 class="_editorHeading2_1q1gx_86" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3. Grievance Procedure</span></h2><h3 class="_editorHeading3_1q1gx_95" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Informal Resolution</span></h3><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Employees are encouraged to raise concerns informally with their line manager first.</span></p><h3 class="_editorHeading3_1q1gx_95" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Formal Grievance</span></h3><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">If informal resolution is not possible:</span></p><ol class="_editorListOrdered_1q1gx_140"><li value="1" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Submit in Writing:</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> The employee should submit their grievance in writing.</span></li><li value="2" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Grievance Meeting:</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> A meeting will be held to discuss the grievance. The employee has the right to be accompanied.</span></li><li value="3" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Outcome:</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> A written response will be provided.</span></li><li value="4" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Appeal:</strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> The employee has the right to appeal the decision.</span></li></ol><h2 class="_editorHeading2_1q1gx_86" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">4. Record Keeping</span></h2><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">All disciplinary and grievance records will be kept confidential and stored securely for the duration required by law.</span></p>	draft	\N	\N	{}		Employment & HR	f	f	\N	46	2025-11-24 09:50:18.701021	27	\N
199	60	1	Incident Responce Procedure	<h1 class="_editorHeading1_1q1gx_77" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Incident Response Procedures</span></h1><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Contents</strong></b></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.2et92p0" class="_editorLink_1q1gx_153" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">1. Purpose 3</span></a></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.tyjcwt" class="_editorLink_1q1gx_153" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">2. Responsibilities 3</span></a></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.3dy6vkm" class="_editorLink_1q1gx_153" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.1 Directors 3</span></a></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.1t3h5sf" class="_editorLink_1q1gx_153" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.3 All Staff 3</span></a></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.4d34og8" class="_editorLink_1q1gx_153" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3. Procedures 3</span></a></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.2s8eyo1" class="_editorLink_1q1gx_153" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.1. Identify a Incident Response/Suspected Incident Response 3</span></a></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.3rdcrjn" class="_editorLink_1q1gx_153" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.2. Reporting an Incident 3</span></a></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.lnxbz9" class="_editorLink_1q1gx_153" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.3. Investigating an Incident 4</span></a></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.1ksv4uv" class="_editorLink_1q1gx_153" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.4. Escalation 4</span></a></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.yc536kuvoh9d" class="_editorLink_1q1gx_153" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.5. Reporting an incident to a customer 4</span></a></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.44sinio" class="_editorLink_1q1gx_153" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Appendix A  Incident Response Notification Form 5</strong></b></a></p><h1 class="_editorHeading1_1q1gx_77" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Incident Response Procedures</span></h1><h1 class="_editorHeading1_1q1gx_77" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Purpose</span></h1><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This document outlines a process for how The Ambassador Platform will ensure the following:</span></p><ul class="_editorListUnordered_1q1gx_133"><li value="1" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Security incident events are detected, reported and monitored consistently</span></li><li value="2" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Incidents are assessed and responded to appropriately</span></li><li value="3" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Action is taken to reduce the impact of a breach</span></li><li value="4" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Relevant breaches are reported to the Information Commissioner within the 72 hour window</span></li><li value="5" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Improvements are made to prevent recurrence</span></li><li value="6" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Improvements are communicated to the wider organisation</span></li></ul><h1 class="_editorHeading1_1q1gx_77" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Responsibilities</span></h1><h2 class="_editorHeading2_1q1gx_86" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.1 Directors</span></h2><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The Directors of the organisation have responsibility for ensuring that any security risks are managed appropriately and that risks are identified and appropriately managed.</span></p><h2 class="_editorHeading2_1q1gx_86" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.3 All Staff</span></h2><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">All users of information assets across the organisation should familiarise themselves with this procedure, be aware of security risks and be vigilant in order to ensure breaches are identified, reported and managed in a timely manner.</span></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Gross negligence and intentional violations (including not reporting incidents/mistakes) are taken seriously and will lead to disciplinary action.</span></p><h1 class="_editorHeading1_1q1gx_77" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Procedures</span></h1><h2 class="_editorHeading2_1q1gx_86" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Identify a Incident Response/Suspected Incident Response</span></h2><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A security incident can happen for a number of reasons, for example:</span></p><ul class="_editorListUnordered_1q1gx_133"><li value="1" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Hacking attack</span></li><li value="2" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Equipment failure</span></li><li value="3" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Human error</span></li></ul><h2 class="_editorHeading2_1q1gx_86" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Reporting an Incident</span></h2><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">It is vital that as soon as an Incident is identified </span><u><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164 _editorTextUnderline_1q1gx_172" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">or suspected</strong></b></u><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> </strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">it is immediately reported to the Data Protection Team.</span></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">As much information as is immediately available should be collated and the Incident Response Notification Form (Appendix A) should be completed and sent via Basecamp as soon as possible (latest within 12 hours of breach identification) to the Director of Engineering (DSO) and CEO (DDOS).</span></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The Director of Engineering and CEO will analyse the form, update the Incident Response Log and ascertain whether any immediate corrective/containment/escalation actions are required.</span></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68"><br></p><h2 class="_editorHeading2_1q1gx_86" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Investigating an Incident</span></h2><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The incident will be assessed. The investigation will:</span></p><ol class="_editorListOrdered_1q1gx_140"><li value="1" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Establish the nature of the incident, the type and impact</span></li><li value="2" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Perform a risk assessment</span></li><li value="3" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Identify actions the organisation needs to take to eliminate the incident</span></li><li value="4" class="_editorListItem_1q1gx_147" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Assess the ongoing risk and actions required to prevent a recurrence of the incident.</span></li></ol><h2 class="_editorHeading2_1q1gx_86" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Escalation</span></h2><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The Incident Response Log will be reviewed on a regular basis by the board of the company who will determine whether any updates to Policy and Procedures are required and coordinate any relevant training.</span></p><h2 class="_editorHeading2_1q1gx_86" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.5. Reporting an incident to a customer</span></h2><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The Director of Engineering will coordinate breach reporting to the Information Commissioner and to all customers as soon as possible, at least within 72 hours via email and phone (if needed).</span></p><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">An incident is also reflected automatically at </span><a href="https://status.theambassadorplatform.com/" class="_editorLink_1q1gx_153" dir="ltr"><u><span class="_editorTextUnderline_1q1gx_172" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">https://status.theambassadorplatform.com/</span></u></a><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> and a customer can sign-up to receive automatic notifications via email, slack, RSS.</span></p><h1 class="_editorHeading1_1q1gx_77" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Appendix A  Incident Response Notification Form</span></h1><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68"><br></p><table class="_editorTable_1q1gx_191" dir="ltr"><colgroup><col><col><col><col><col><col><col><col><col><col><col></colgroup><tbody><tr dir="ltr"><th class="_editorTableCell_1q1gx_200 _editorTableCellHeader_1q1gx_208" dir="ltr" style="border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);"><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Date</strong></b></p></th><th class="_editorTableCell_1q1gx_200 _editorTableCellHeader_1q1gx_208" dir="ltr" style="border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);"><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Time of Breach</strong></b></p></th><th class="_editorTableCell_1q1gx_200 _editorTableCellHeader_1q1gx_208" dir="ltr" style="border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);"><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Overview</strong></b></p></th><th class="_editorTableCell_1q1gx_200 _editorTableCellHeader_1q1gx_208" dir="ltr" style="border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);"><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">How Discovered?</strong></b></p></th><th class="_editorTableCell_1q1gx_200 _editorTableCellHeader_1q1gx_208" dir="ltr" style="border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);"><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="_editorTextBold_1q1gx_164" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Person Reporting</strong></b></p></th><th class="_editorTableCell_1q1gx_200 _editorTableCellHeader_1q1gx_208" dir="ltr" style="border: 1px solid black; width: 75px; vertical-align: top; text-align: start; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245);"><p class="_editorParagraph_1q1gx_68" dir="ltr"><b>