79	13	3	Data Breach Procedure	<h1 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading1" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Personal Data Breach Procedures</span></h1><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Contents</strong></b></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.gjdgxs" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorLink"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">1. </span></a><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Introduction 3</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.2et92p0" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorLink"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">2. </span></a><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Purpose 3</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.tyjcwt" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorLink"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3. </span></a><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Responsibilities 3</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.3dy6vkm" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorLink"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.1 </span></a><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Directors 3</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.1t3h5sf" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorLink"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.3 </span></a><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">All Staff 3</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.4d34og8" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorLink"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">4. </span></a><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Procedures 5</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.2s8eyo1" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorLink"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">4.1. </span></a><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Identify a Personal Data Breach/Suspected Personal Data Breach 5</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.3rdcrjn" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorLink"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">4.2. </span></a><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Reporting an Incident 5</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.lnxbz9" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorLink"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">4.3. </span></a><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Investigating an Incident 5</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.35nkun2" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorLink"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">4.4. </span></a><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Reporting Breach to the Information Commissioner or Data Subject 6</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><a href="#_heading=h.1ksv4uv" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorLink"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">4.5. </span></a><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Escalation 6</span></p><h1 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading1" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Personal Data Breach Procedures</span></h1><h1 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading1" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Introduction</span></h1><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">As an organisation that processes personal data The Ambassador Platform must ensure appropriate measures are in place to protect against accidental or unlawful destruction, loss, alteration, unauthorised disclosure of, or access to, personal data. The General Data Protection Regulation specifies that all breaches (except those </span><i><em class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextItalic" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">unlikely to result in a risk to the rights and freedoms of natural persons) </em></i><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">should be reported to the Information Commissioner </span><i><em class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextItalic" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">without undue delaynot later than 72 hours after having become aware of it.sdfsdf</em></i></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph"><br></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">As a Data Processor, we will support our customers and partners with providing them with full information about data breaches as soon as possible, at least within this 72 hour period.</span></p><h1 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading1" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Purpose</span></h1><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This document outlines a process for how The Ambassador Platform will ensure the following:</span></p><ul class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListUnordered"><li value="1" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Data breach events are detected, reported and monitored consistently</span></li><li value="2" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Incidents are assessed and responded to appropriately</span></li><li value="3" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Action is taken to reduce the impact of a breach</span></li><li value="4" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Relevant breaches are reported to the Information Commissioner within the 72 hour window</span></li><li value="5" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Improvements are made to prevent recurrence</span></li><li value="6" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Improvements are communicated to the wider organisation</span></li></ul><h1 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading1" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Responsibilities</span></h1><h2 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.1 Directors</span></h2><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The Directors of the organisation have responsibility for ensuring that any privacy risks are managed appropriately and that risks are identified and appropriately managed.</span></p><h2 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">3.3 All Staff</span></h2><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">All users of information assets across the organisation should familiarise themselves with this procedure, be aware of privacy risks and be vigilant in order to ensure breaches are identified, reported and managed in a timely manner.</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">At The Ambassador Platform we want an open and honest culture where people feel comfortable to report mistakes. We support this with training for all employees on data security which is renewed on an at least bi-annually basis.</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Gross negligence and intentional violations (including not reporting incidents/mistakes) are taken seriously and will lead to disciplinary action.</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Additionally we have Cyber Insurance to ensure The Ambassador Platform receives expert third party support in the event of a security breach and cost concerns are not a factor in the remedial action.</span></p><h1 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading1" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Procedures</span></h1><h2 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Identify a Personal Data Breach/Suspected Personal Data Breach</span></h2><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A personal data breach can happen for a number of reasons, for example:</span></p><ul class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListUnordered"><li value="1" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Loss or theft of data or equipment on which data is stored, or through which it can be accessed</span></li><li value="2" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Loss or theft of paper files</span></li><li value="3" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Hacking attack</span></li><li value="4" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Inappropriate access controls allowing unauthorised/unnecessary access to data</span></li><li value="5" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Equipment failure</span></li><li value="6" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Human error</span></li><li value="7" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Unforeseen circumstances such as a fire or flood</span></li></ul><h2 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Reporting an Incident</span></h2><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">It is vital that as soon as a Personal Data Breach is identified </span><u><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextUnderline" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">or suspected</strong></b></u><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> </strong></b><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">it is immediately reported to the Data Protection Team. In order to improve our understanding of the risks to data and address them before breaches occur we would also encourage individuals to report near misses (i.e. incidents which have almost resulted in a data breach except for an intervention or luck). Near misses should be reported using the same form and process as an actual breach highlighting clearly that the incident is a near miss. The General Data Protection Regulation requires that all relevant breaches are reported to the supervisory authority (the Information Commissioner) </span><i><em class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextItalic" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">without undue delay.., </em></i><i><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextItalic" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">not later than 72 hours</strong></b></i><i><em class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextItalic" style="white-space: pre-wrap;"> after having become aware of it.</em></i></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">As much information as is immediately available should be collated and the Personal Data Breach Notification Form (Appendix A) should be completed and sent via Basecamp as soon as possible (latest within 12 hours of breach identification) to the Director of Engineering (DSO) and CEO (DDOS).</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The Director of Engineering and CEO will analyse the form, update the Personal Data Breach Log and ascertain whether any immediate corrective/containment/escalation actions are required.</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph"><br></p><h2 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Investigating an Incident</span></h2><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The incident will be assessed as to whether a full investigation into the breach is required.</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The investigation will:</span></p><ol class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListOrdered"><li value="1" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Establish the nature of the incident, the type and volume of data involved and the identity of the data subjects</span></li><li value="2" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Consider the extent of a breach and data involved</span></li><li value="3" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Perform a risk assessment</span></li><li value="4" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Identify actions the organisation needs to take to contain the breach and recover information</span></li><li value="5" class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorListItem" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Assess the ongoing risk and actions required to prevent a recurrence of the incident.</span></li></ol><h2 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Reporting Breach to the Information Commissioner or Data Subject</span></h2><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The first action taken will be to contact our Cyber Insurers, Hiscox 24/7 hotline to immediately inform them of the incident and share the information we have. This insurance provides us with immediate access to expert advice who will advise us on best practice for remedial action, in line with this policy.</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The Director of Engineering will coordinate breach reporting to the Information Commissioner and to all customers as soon as possible, at least within 72 hours via email and phone (if needed).</span></p><h2 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading2" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Escalation</span></h2><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The Personal Data Breach Log will be reviewed on a regular basis by the board of the company who will determine whether any updates to Policy and Procedures are required and coordinate any relevant training.</span></p><h1 class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorHeading1" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Appendix A  Personal Data Breach Notification Form</span></h1><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph"><br></p><table class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTable" dir="ltr"><colgroup><col><col><col><col><col><col><col><col><col><col><col></colgroup><tbody><tr dir="ltr"><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Date</strong></b></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Time of Breach</strong></b></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Overview</strong></b></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">How Discovered?</strong></b></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Person Reporting</strong></b></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;"># of records</strong></b></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">People Affected</strong></b></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">System/Application/Database Involved</strong></b></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Types of Data</strong></b></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Root Cause?</strong></b></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><b><strong class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTextBold" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Action Taken</strong></b></p></th></tr><tr dir="ltr"><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">17.02.2025</span></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">23:11</span></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">some passwords related to old and unused domains have been compromised</span></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">These emails were created on a Google Workspace account that is used as an identity provider. Therefore, when the passwords for these emails were compromised, Google, which continuously monitors password safety, automatically informed us about it.</span></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">George Olesen, CEO</span></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">7 records</span></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">none. mostly system emails were used for demo accounts - nothing related to customer data, PII, or sensitive information</span></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">dashboard.theambassadorpaltform.com</span></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">password to emails</span></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">MITM Attack or Weak or Reused Passwords and Lack of Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) as these accounts were not related to any real customer or any other form of sensitive information.</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Definitely not</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">a credential exposure from a 3-party breach (tested on respective services that validate it)</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A phishing attack</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Malware or key logger</span></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Employees warned</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Passwords updated</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">MFA installed</span></p></th></tr></tbody></table><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph"><br></p>	published	\N	\N	{}	Executive / Leadership	Data Protection & Privacy	f	t	\N	14	2025-10-01 10:21:58.60785	5	\N
126	41	3	Disciplinary and Grievance Policy	<h1>Disciplinary and Grievance Policy</h1>\n<h2>1. Purpose</h2>\n<p>This policy outlines the procedures for handling disciplinary matters and employee grievances to ensure fairness and consistency, in line with the Acas Code of Practice.</p>\n<h2>2. Disciplinary Procedure</h2>\n<h3>Informal Action</h3>\n<p>Minor misconduct will be addressed informally through discussion and counselling.</p>\n<h3>Formal Action</h3>\n<p>For more serious issues, the following stages will be followed:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Investigation:</strong> A fair and impartial investigation will be conducted.</li>\n<li><strong>Written Notification:</strong> The employee will be notified in writing of the allegations.</li>\n<li><strong>Disciplinary Hearing:</strong> The employee has the right to be accompanied by a colleague or trade union representative.</li>\n<li><strong>Outcome:</strong> A written decision will be provided, which may include:<ul>\n<li>First Written Warning</li>\n<li>Final Written Warning</li>\n<li>Dismissal (for gross misconduct)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Appeal:</strong> The employee has the right to appeal the decision.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>3. Grievance Procedure</h2>\n<h3>Informal Resolution</h3>\n<p>Employees are encouraged to raise concerns informally with their line manager first.</p>\n<h3>Formal Grievance</h3>\n<p>If informal resolution is not possible:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Submit in Writing:</strong> The employee should submit their grievance in writing.</li>\n<li><strong>Grievance Meeting:</strong> A meeting will be held to discuss the grievance. The employee has the right to be accompanied.</li>\n<li><strong>Outcome:</strong> A written response will be provided.</li>\n<li><strong>Appeal:</strong> The employee has the right to appeal the decision.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>4. Record Keeping</h2>\n<p>All disciplinary and grievance records will be kept confidential and stored securely for the duration required by law.</p>\n	publishe