ule__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">MITM Attack or Weak or Reused Passwords and Lack of Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) as these accounts were not related to any real customer or any other form of sensitive information.</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Definitely not</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">a credential exposure from a 3-party breach (tested on respective services that validate it)</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A phishing attack</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Malware or key logger</span></p></th><th class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCell c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorTableCellHeader" dir="ltr" style="width: 75px; background-color: rgb(242, 243, 245); border: 1px solid black; vertical-align: top; text-align: start;"><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Employees warned</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Passwords updated</span></p><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph" dir="ltr"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">MFA installed</span></p></th></tr></tbody></table><p class="c1h__module__WysiwygEditor_editorParagraph"><br></p>	published	\N	\N	{}	Executive / Leadership	Data Protection & Privacy	f	t	\N	14	2025-10-01 10:21:58.60785	5	\N
