193	58	1	No Casino Policy	<h1>No Casino Policy</h1>\n<h2>Purpose</h2>\n<p>The purpose of this policy is to outline the expectations and guidelines for employees regarding the use of corporate resources and conduct related to casino activities. This policy aims to ensure that all employees are aware of and comply with the standards of integrity and ethical conduct expected by the organization.</p>\n<h2>Scope</h2>\n<p>This policy applies to all employees of the organization, including full-time, part-time, temporary, and contract employees, across all departments and locations.</p>\n<h2>Policy Statement</h2>\n<p>The Human Resources department is committed to maintaining a professional and ethical work environment. Employees are expected to focus on their responsibilities and strive to perform their duties to the best of their ability without engaging in activities that could compromise their professional judgment or the reputation of the organization.</p>\n<h2>Key Requirements</h2>\n<h3>Professional Conduct</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Employees are expected to execute their duties diligently and responsibly. This entails giving their utmost effort at work and maintaining professionalism at all times.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Prohibition on Casino Expenditures</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>The use of corporate credit cards for personal activities, including but not limited to casino gambling or any form of gambling-related expenditures, is strictly prohibited.</li>\n<li>Any costs associated with casino activities or related entertainment must be borne personally by the employee and should not, under any circumstances, be charged to the organization.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Consequences of Policy Violation</h2>\n<p>Violations of this policy may result in disciplinary action, up to and including termination of employment. In cases where the corporate credit card is used in violation of this policy, the employee will be required to reimburse the full amount charged and may face additional consequences as deemed appropriate by the organization.</p>\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Employees are responsible for understanding and adhering to this policy.</li>\n<li>Managers and supervisors are responsible for ensuring their teams understand the policy and for enforcing compliance within their respective departments.</li>\n<li>The Human Resources department will oversee the dissemination of this policy and address any questions or concerns related to its implementation.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Review and Amendments</h2>\n<p>This policy will be reviewed annually and updated as necessary to ensure compliance with organizational standards and regulatory requirements. Changes to the policy will be communicated promptly to all employees.</p>\n<h2>Contact Information</h2>\n<p>For any questions or further clarification regarding this policy, employees are encouraged to contact the Human Resources department.</p>\n	draft	2025-11-24	2025-11-30	{}	Human Resources	Human Resources	f	f	\N	46	2025-11-24 09:53:35.118636	27	\N
